SIMPLE: uniformly
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Uniformly
<hw>U"ni*form`ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In a uniform
manner; without variation or diversity; by a regular, constant, or
common ratio of change; with even tenor; <as>as, a temper
<ex>uniformly</ex> mild</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To vary uniformly</b></col> <fld>(Math.)</fld>, <cd>to
vary with the ratio of the corresponding increments constant; -- said of
two dependent quantities with regard to each other.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unifromness</ent>⟦br⟧
